<br>
The difference, here, is that Clerics and Enchanters are SUPPORT classes.. they are not supposed to be offense oriented.  And they do support work VERY well in PvE AND PvP.<br>
<br>
Wizards ARE supposed to be offense oriented, but obviously you have never played a wizard because you would realize that in PvP, wizards suck most of their lives.  It IS a very frustrating class to play, and very frustrating to pvp with especially.   You are not wanted very much in PvP or PvE for groups because you don't really add much other than firepower that takes a LONG time to reload and is resistable.  Melee damage is much better when you can add some melee-friendly support classes.  And as a stand alone pvp class, wizards get a few one shot spells, and then they are at the mercy of the opposition.<br>
<br>
The reason wizards complain about offensive power is because they are an OFFENSE oriented class.  You should fear a wizard.. but most people dont.<br>
<br>
It's pretty obvious that wizards are goign to have better offensive capabillites than enchanters or clerics... they are intended that way. <p><P><html><center><a href="http://angerthas.com/"><center><IMG SRC="http://angerthas.com/horsesig.gif"></center></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uagrul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Agrul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 11:59:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards...hah!</span><hr size=1> They fucked up the patch.<br>
