<br>
Before patch:<br>
A level 25 melee in full resist gear doesn't fare <b>any</b> differently vs. a level 40 caster than a level 25 melee does naked.  His presence or lack of gear has no affect on the outcome of the encounter.<br>
<br>
<br>
One way or another, they're attempting to make the the game more uniform, in treating resists closer to the way they do AC.<br>
<br>
<br>
I go after an awesome weapon, and whether I'm attacking a 10 or a 60, I'm still swinging faster, and connecting for more damage (on average).<br>
I go after some awesome AC gear and whether I'm being beat on by a level 10 or a level 60, I'm still getting hit less often, and for less damage (on average).<br>
I go after some awesome resist gear at 30, and I'm resisting no more than before the level 10s' spells (because I resisted them all before) or the level 60s' spells (because I never resisted any before).<br>
<br>
There was something wrong with the discrepancy described here, and even if they didn't fix it properly in this last patch, the fact that they're taking steps towards fixing it is what matters to me...<br>
